---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import site from '../data/site.json';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | SimploSite"
  description="Terms of service for SimploSite website services and use of simplosite.ca."
  canonicalPath="/terms-of-service/"
>
  <section class="section legal-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">SimploSite · Terms of Service</p>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="lead">These terms describe the basic conditions for using this website and working with SimploSite.</p>

    <div class="card legal-card">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 5, 2026</p>
      <p><strong>Website:</strong> {site.domain}</p>
      <p><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-copy">
      <h2>Use of this website</h2>
      <p>This website is provided for general information about SimploSite and its services. You agree not to misuse the website, attempt unauthorized access, interfere with its operation, or use it for unlawful purposes.</p>

      <h2>Service requests and estimates</h2>
      <p>Submitting an inquiry or requesting an estimate does not create a client relationship by itself. Work, pricing, timelines, deliverables, and payment terms must be confirmed separately in writing before a project or subscription begins.</p>

      <h2>Client responsibilities</h2>
      <p>Clients are responsible for providing accurate information, text, images, approvals, access, business details, and any materials needed to complete the agreed work. Clients are also responsible for ensuring that their business information, claims, licenses, permits, and legal obligations are accurate and current.</p>

      <h2>Payments and subscriptions</h2>
      <p>When a payment or subscription is offered, the amount, billing interval, trial period, renewal terms, and cancellation conditions are presented before payment. Payments may be processed by Stripe or another payment provider. The payment provider may apply its own terms and policies.</p>

      <h2>No guarantee of results</h2>
      <p>SimploSite works to provide clear and useful websites, but does not guarantee a specific number of visits, calls, quote requests, clients, sales, revenue, ranking position, or business result.</p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>Some services may rely on third-party providers such as hosting, domain, email, payment, communication, or business tools. SimploSite is not responsible for interruptions, policy changes, or actions by third-party providers outside its reasonable control.</p>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>Unless otherwise agreed in writing, SimploSite retains rights to its methods, templates, processes, code structures, and reusable materials. Client-provided materials remain the responsibility of the client, and the client confirms that they have the right to use any materials supplied.</p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, SimploSite is not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including lost profits, lost revenue, business interruption, or loss of data arising from the use of this website or services.</p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these terms from time to time. The updated version will be posted on this page with a revised date.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about these terms can be sent to <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
